# WB Component Loader

Auto-discovers and loads WB components using the wb-event-log architecture pattern.

## üöÄ Quick Start

### Single Line Setup:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <script type="module" src="../../component-loader.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Components automatically load! -->
    <wb-layout layout="top-nav">
        <wb-nav items='[...]'></wb-nav>
        <main>Content</main>
    </wb-layout>
</body>
</html>
```

## üìã Features

‚úÖ **Zero Configuration** - Just include the script
‚úÖ **Convention-Based** - Uses `components/wb-xyz/wb-xyz.js` pattern
‚úÖ **Auto-Discovery** - Scans HTML for `<wb-*>` tags
‚úÖ **Dynamic Detection** - MutationObserver for runtime additions
‚úÖ **Single Instance** - Only initializes once
‚úÖ **Debug Helpers** - Console methods for troubleshooting
‚úÖ **Event-Driven** - Dispatches `wb:component-loaded` events

## üéØ Architecture Pattern

Follows the same pattern as `wb-event-log` auto-injection:

```javascript
// Static properties (like wb-event-log)
WBComponentLoader.loaded        // Set of loaded components
WBComponentLoader.observer      // MutationObserver instance
WBComponentLoader._initialized  // Initialization flag

// Public API (like WBBaseComponent.getGlobalEventLog())
WBComponentLoader.getLoadedComponents()    // Get array of loaded components
WBComponentLoader.loadComponent('wb-xyz')  // Load component manually
WBComponentLoader.showLoadedComponents()   // Debug: show what's loaded
WBComponentLoader.showStatus()             // Debug: show loader status
```

## üîß Debug Commands

